tweet_raw: 3. Deepfake videos on YouTube and other social mediaDeepfake videos on platforms like YouTube and social media have become a scam tactic in the recovering crypto market. A recent example is the Solana fraud where deepfake videos of Solana co-founder Anatoly Yakovenko promised to double funds for anyone who scanned a QR code. Unfortunately those who transferred their funds to the fraudsters did not receive their tokens back. Similar deepfake videos featuring influencers like CZ and Elon Musk have also surfaced. As AI technology advances these realistic deepfake videos may become a prevalent form of scam in the potentially bullish year of 2024.

tweet_raw: 10. #Render (#RNDR) Render is an Ethereum blockchain-based distributed GPU network that functions as an essential platform for animation VFX rendering and motion graphics. Its native token Render (RNDR) serves as a utility token specifically designed for utilization within the Render network. The network comprises two primary stakeholders: 1) Creators and 2) Node operators. Through the Render network creators gain access to the immense GPU power available on the network enabling them to generate high-quality images and visually captivating content at exceptional speeds and reduced costs. On the other hand node operators lease out their GPU processing power to these creators and in return receive render tokens as rewards.At present the trading value of Render (RNDR) stands at $4.55 contributing to an impressive market capitalization of $1.7 billion at the time of writing.

tweet_text: 8 thegraph grt the graph is a crucial tool for organizing and retrieving data on networks like ethereum and ipfs playing a key role in the defi and web3 ecosystem it allows developers to easily create and share open apis called subgraphs enabling applications to smoothly access blockchain data using graphql while theres a current hosted service the project plans to launch a decentralized network soon the protocol already works with ethereum ipfs and poa and more networks are in the pipeline with over 3000 subgraphs deployed by various developers for different dapps the graph has seen significant growth with usage increasing by over 50 monthly and surpassing 7 billion queries in september 2020 the graph has a global community including 200 indexer nodes and 2000 curators as of october 2020 showcasing widespread involvement to fuel network development the graph secured funding from community members strategic vcs and influential figures in the blockchain space such as coinbase ventures dcg framework and parafi capital among others the graph foundation successfully raised around 25m through a public grt sale in november 2020 underscoring strong financial support and community engagement for the project
tweet_raw: 8. #TheGraph (#GRT)The Graph is a crucial tool for organizing and retrieving data on networks like #Ethereum and IPFS playing a key role in the DeFi and #Web3 ecosystem. It allows developers to easily create and share open APIs called subgraphs enabling applications to smoothly access blockchain data using #GraphQL. While there’s a current hosted service the project plans to launch a decentralized network soon. The protocol already works with Ethereum IPFS and POA and more networks are in the pipeline. With over 3000 subgraphs deployed by various developers for different #DApps The Graph has seen significant growth with usage increasing by over 50% monthly and surpassing 7 billion queries in September 2020.The Graph has a global community including 200 Indexer Nodes and 2000 Curators as of October 2020 showcasing widespread involvement. To fuel network development The Graph secured funding from community members strategic VCs and influential figures in the blockchain space such as #Coinbase Ventures DCG Framework and #ParaFi Capital among others. The Graph Foundation successfully raised around $25M through a public GRT Sale in November 2020 underscoring strong financial support and community engagement for the project.

tweet_text: binance freezes 42 million in stolen xrp  binance the worlds largest cryptocurrency exchange has frozen 42 million in xrp tokens that were stolen from the wallet of ripple labs cofounder chris larsen  the theft occurred on january 30 2024 when hackers gained access to larsens personal accounts and transferred the xrp tokens to a number of different wallets binance was able to identify and freeze the tokens thanks to its advanced blockchain analytics tools  we are committed to protecting our users and their assets said binance ceo richard teng we will continue to work with law enforcement to investigate this crime and bring the perpetrators to justice  the theft is the latest in a series of highprofile cryptocurrency hacks in 2018 hackers stole 534 million from the japanese cryptocurrency exchange coincheck and in 2019 hackers stole 40 million from the cryptocurrency exchange binance
tweet_raw: Binance Freezes $4.2 Million in Stolen XRPBinance the worlds largest cryptocurrency exchange has frozen $4.2 million in XRP tokens that were stolen from the wallet of Ripple Labs co-founder Chris Larsen.The theft occurred on January 30 2024 when hackers gained access to Larsens personal accounts and transferred the XRP tokens to a number of different wallets. Binance was able to identify and freeze the tokens thanks to its advanced blockchain analytics tools.We are committed to protecting our users and their assets said Binance CEO Richard Teng. We will continue to work with law enforcement to investigate this crime and bring the perpetrators to justice.The theft is the latest in a series of high-profile cryptocurrency hacks. In 2018 hackers stole $534 million from the Japanese cryptocurrency exchange Coincheck. And in 2019 hackers stole $40 million from the cryptocurrency exchange Binance.

tweet_raw: Indeed.  “Efficient Markets” assumes a fixed pool of market participants.  That’s mostly sensible for public equities.  But the growth story of cryptocurrency has largely been one of broadening ripples of adoption as ever growing populations are able to buy and store it with new tech front ends and financial wrappers.  There are trillions of dollars of wealth in the hands of institutions and individuals who will happily buy $10m of an ETF on the NYSE through their standard broker but wouldn’t dream of sending that to Coinbase.   And before that…Coinbase gave access to Bitcoin to people who wouldn’t dream of mining or using scam and hacked exchanges.

tweet_raw: I bought some Pesos in Argentina 🇦🇷 via a P2P exchange using USDT on Tron.  Heres my experience 👇👇👇First of all why go P2P? Because the official USD-ARS exchange rate is 2.5-3x worse than the blue dollar rate. I actually tried: I withdrew 30€ from an ATM paid 10€ in international fees and got the bad exchange rate. Absolutely unusable ❌❌❌P2P process:- Comms with seller via Telegram (with help from a local friend)- Minimum amount was 200 USD payable with USDT on Tron.- Delivery to my address Challenge: How do I get USDT on Tron? Never used it before🧐The whole process below took less than 15min including thinking and cursing.1) Can I use @MetaMask? No Tron does not support MM.. meh❌2) I can use @exodus_io multichain wallet. Set up: 2min  ✅ 3) Now to getting Usdt. Want to swap mainnet ETH for Usdt via Metamask... 20-40 USD fee. No thanks! ❌4) I have some ETH on @BuildOnBase... but Exodus does not support USDT on Base... ❌ 5) I withdraw ETH from Base to Exodus --> takes 1min ✅ 6) Swap ETH.base for USDT.trx in Exodus. Uff 7 USD fee on a USD 200 swap 🙈 ⚠️7) Ok now I want to send USDT.trx to the seller... error: need TRX for fees 🤨❌8) Try swapping some USDT.trx to TRX on Exodus... need to swap at least 100 USD worth (waaay to much for a one-time thing) 🫤 and it seems need TRX first for that as well?? ❌9) Ok I can buy TRX via Exodus onramp integration. Uses @RampNetwork for TRX - supports Revolut. I select Revolut enter my name Revolut app pops up I approve the transfer get TRX in Exodus within 1 min ✅  I only bought 20 USD worth but **no KYC** (either small amount OR they use existing Revolut KYC... The latter would be amazing need check). This was actually a positive surprise. Kudos to Ramp👍10) Send 200 USDT to seller... paying $1.30 in TRX fees⚠️ lol this was supposed to be cheap?11) Send tx id and explorer link to seller✅11) Cash delivered to my doorstep ✅Overall worked well enough... But theres lots of room for improvement. I could have just used an onramp to buy USDT - but the fees would have been high. I did not want to use an exchange because I keep no assets there so it would have taken ages to deposit and withdraw. Paying with #BTC was not supported and depositing BTC into Exodus would have taken too long. Maybe Lightning would have worked.. but Im not sure if any Tron wallets also support LN? Closing thoughts:The picture below is 200USD in Pesos (168k ARS)...  For comparison  a nice meal (steak side drink) costs 10-15k ARS.This was an eye opening experience and a good reminder of why I work on #Bitcoin and web3 infrastructure. Mad respect for the Argentinian community for resisting the economic challenges.

tweet_raw: 154 #dailyartpiece #theoldmasters Roger van der Weyden ( about 1400-1464) Flanders Apparition of Christ to his Mother about 1430Metropolitan Museum of Art NY Rogier van der Weyden or Roger de la Pasture (1399 or 1400 – 18 June 1464) was an early Netherlandish painter whose surviving works consist mainly of religious triptychs altarpieces and commissioned single and diptych portraits. He was highly successful in his lifetime; his paintings were exported to Italy and Spain and he received commissions from amongst others Philip the Good Netherlandish nobility and foreign princes. By the latter half of the 15th century he had eclipsed Jan van Eyck in popularity. However his fame lasted only until the 17th century and largely due to changing taste he was almost totally forgotten by the mid-18th century. His reputation was slowly rebuilt during the 200 years that followed; today he is known with Robert Campin and van Eyck as the third (by birth date) of the three great Early Flemish artists (Vlaamse Primitieven or Flemish Primitives) and widely as the most influential Northern painter of the 15th century.

tweet_text: bifrost on polkadot solutions for liquidity and interoperability  bifrost is a web3 derivatives protocol that offers innovative solutions for liquidity and interoperability within the polkadot ecosystem it focuses on three key areas  1 liquid staking  allows users to gain liquidity from their staked dot and ksm tokens without the need to unstake them provides liquid derivatives vdot and vksm that represent staking participation unlocking capital for defi lending and other activities increases the staking rate on the network by removing the liquidity barrier  2 crosschain interoperability  allows users to transfer staked assets and liquid derivatives between different blockchains in polkadot and kusama facilitates participation in multiple chains without the need to restake their tokens promotes interoperability and efficiency across the polkadot ecosystem  3 ecosystem solutions  offers synthetic units of account scus that represent the value of a basket of assets enables the creation of new defi products such as index funds and leveraged derivatives expands the possibilities of the polkadot ecosystem for financial innovation in summary bifrost  unlocks liquidity from staked tokens boosting participation and defi usage facilitates the transfer of assets between chains improving interoperability powers innovation in the polkadot ecosystem with new financial solutions bifrost has become a fundamental piece for the evolution of polkadot by unlocking the potential of liquid staking and interoperability  bifrostfinance bifrostfinance polkaversecom12434bifrost polkaverse subsocial
tweet_raw: #Bifrost on #Polkadot: Solutions for Liquidity and Interoperability#Bifrost is a #web3 derivatives protocol that offers innovative solutions for liquidity and interoperability within the #Polkadot ecosystem. It focuses on three key areas:1. Liquid #Staking:Allows users to gain liquidity from their staked $DOT and $KSM tokens without the need to unstake them.Provides liquid derivatives (vDOT and vKSM) that represent #staking participation unlocking capital for DeFi lending and other activities.Increases the staking rate on the network by removing the liquidity barrier.2. Cross-chain Interoperability:Allows users to transfer #staked assets and liquid derivatives between different blockchains in #Polkadot and #Kusama.Facilitates participation in multiple chains without the need to re-stake their tokens.Promotes interoperability and efficiency across the #Polkadot ecosystem.3. Ecosystem Solutions:Offers synthetic units of account (SCUs) that represent the value of a basket of assets.Enables the creation of new #DeFi products such as index funds and leveraged derivatives.Expands the possibilities of the #Polkadot ecosystem for financial innovation.In summary #Bifrost:Unlocks liquidity from staked tokens boosting participation and #DeFi usage.Facilitates the transfer of assets between chains improving interoperability.Powers innovation in the #Polkadot ecosystem with new financial solutions.#Bifrost has become a fundamental piece for the evolution of #Polkadot by unlocking the potential of liquid #staking and interoperability.@BifrostFinancebifrost.finance/polkaverse.com/12434/bifrost…#PolkaVerse #Subsocial

tweet_raw: I bought some Pesos in Argentina 🇦🇷 via a P2P exchange using USDT on Tron.  Heres my experience 👇👇👇First of all why go P2P? Because the official USD-ARS exchange rate is 2.5-3x worse than the blue dollar rate. I actually tried: I withdrew 30€ from an ATM paid 10€ in international fees and got the bad exchange rate. Absolutely unusable ❌❌❌P2P process:- Comms with seller via Telegram (with help from a local friend)- Minimum amount was 200 USD payable with USDT on Tron.- Delivery to my address Challenge: How do I get USDT on Tron? Never used it before🧐The whole process below took less than 15min including thinking and cursing.1) Can I use @MetaMask? No Tron does not support MM.. meh❌2) I can use @exodus_io multichain wallet. Set up: 2min  ✅ 3) Now to getting Usdt. Want to swap mainnet ETH for Usdt via Metamask... 20-40 USD fee. No thanks! ❌4) I have some ETH on @BuildOnBase... but Exodus does not support USDT on Base... ❌ 5) I withdraw ETH from Base to Exodus --> takes 1min ✅ 6) Swap ETH.base for USDT.trx in Exodus. Uff 7 USD fee on a USD 200 swap 🙈 ⚠️7) Ok now I want to send USDT.trx to the seller... error: need TRX for fees 🤨❌8) Try swapping some USDT.trx to TRX on Exodus... need to swap at least 100 USD worth (waaay to much for a one-time thing) 🫤 and it seems need TRX first for that as well?? ❌9) Ok I can buy TRX via Exodus onramp integration. Uses @RampNetwork for TRX - supports Revolut. I select Revolut enter my name Revolut app pops up I approve the transfer get TRX in Exodus within 1 min ✅  I only bought 20 USD worth but **no KYC** (either small amount OR they use existing Revolut KYC... The latter would be amazing need check). This was actually a positive surprise. Kudos to Ramp👍10) Send 200 USDT to seller... paying $1.30 in TRX fees⚠️ lol this was supposed to be cheap?11) Send tx id and explorer link to seller✅11) Cash delivered to my doorstep ✅Overall worked well enough... But theres lots of room for improvement. I could have just used an onramp to buy USDT - but the fees would have been high. I did not want to use an exchange because I keep no assets there so it would have taken ages to deposit and withdraw. Paying with #BTC was not supported and depositing BTC into Exodus would have taken too long. Maybe Lightning would have worked.. but Im not sure if any Tron wallets also support LN? Closing thoughts:The picture below is 200USD in Pesos (168k ARS)...  For comparison  a nice meal (steak side drink) costs 10-15k ARS.This was an eye opening experience and a good reminder of why I work on #Bitcoin and web3 infrastructure. Mad respect for the Argentinian community for resisting the economic challenges.

tweet_raw: On Nov 22nd Nancy Pelosi and her husband bought Nvidia $NVDA calls a leveraged bet Nvidia would go up. Since then Nvidia is up 77%. Her calls have made her $1.3 million over SIX times her salary in 78 days.I want to give you the history of Pelosi her $NVDA trading and show the conflicts of Congress:Let’s start in December 2021. After a history of unusual trading from Visa trading during the GFC and buying before stimulus bills Nancy Pelosi was asked if she thinks US Congress members should trade despite legislative conflicts by Bryan Metzger.She said We are a free market economy. Congress should be able to participate in that. Insane.In Jan 2022 Unusual Whales releases their most famous trading report showing Congress beat the market. Nancy Pelosi is listed as the fifth best trader in Congress.That report creates a flurry of media and outrage while the report continues to go viral. Within seven days of publishing five new bills banning members of Congress from trading are proposed.In the summer of 2022 it is revealed that Nancy Pelosi was trading millions of dollars of $NVDA Nvidia before voting on a US semiconductor bill by the Biden administration.We reported on her trading to outrage by the public. Interestingly for the first time in history a few days later Nancy Pelosi disclosed trades made on the same day they were made. This is likely the fastest disclosure in history of US Congress. She reported that she sold out of her Nvidia position the first time she divested from conflicts in her portfolio. Despite taking 45 days for every other disclosure she made this one instantly. Hilarious.One month later Nancy Pelosi proposed alongside Representative Lofgren her own Congressional trading ban a bill which was incredibly weak and filled with loopholes.And then Pelosi stopped trading. Well until her $NVDA leveraged bet.One week after Chinese President Xi visits her home state of California and before Biden announces new US semiconductor focuses her husband decided to buy two million dollars of deep in-the-money Nvidia calls the same company she divested from due to conflicts a year earlier. What’s worse On Dec 11th before she bought in November U.S. Commerce Secretary Raimondo said that Nvidia could sell slower AI chips to China to comply with US export controls. And then on Dec 28th NVDA launched a modified version of an advanced chip precisely to get around US restrictions. Nvidia now has released new US chips and has hit all time highs. Of course none of this is insider trading but it does seem unusual especially given scrutiny of Nvida by the government.Why does she trade ITM tech calls you may ask? It allows for one to be bullish with less capital upfront and the contracts move 1 delta to the stock. We wrote more about it on our research site which you can find in our bio.One terrible thing about this trade is that it was done when Congress was in session!!!!!! You can use Unusual Whales to find the exact price she paid for her options and leveraged bets.If you think that one of the most powerful politicians in the US can or even should have leveraged bets over an incredibly important company to US infrastructure that is okay. But there might be something worthwhile in understanding how members of Congress trade and the data suggests as such. Pelosi herself has lost a ton on trades including when she divested from $NVDA last year and yet despite that she decided to enter into it again.And so we will keep reporting on Pelosi and Congress and the history of unusual trading. Pelosis portfolio itself is up around 88% over twelve months. If you want to find and follow her portfolio you can do so on Unusual Whales in our Portfolio tab.Pelosi has made likely ten million this year alone off her tech portfolio with a networth close to likely a quarter of billion. No matter what trade or conflict though I will report on it. If you believe this is an important issue I ask you share this tweet with your friends and family.Congress cannot hide from me I will continue to report on the data and I will not stop until Congress is banned from trading.

tweet_text: the cone nebula from hubble image credit hubble legacy archive nasa esa  processing  licence judy schmidt  explanation stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the cone nebula cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars the cone nebula a wellknown example lies within the bright galactic starforming region ngc 2264 the cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this closeup composite of several observations from the earthorbiting hubble space telescope while the cone nebula about 2500 lightyears away in monoceros is around 7 lightyears long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 25 lightyears across in our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the alpha centauri star system the massive star ngc 2264 irs seen by hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the cone nebula and lies off the top of the image the cone nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas
tweet_raw: The Cone Nebula from HubbleImage Credit: Hubble Legacy Archive NASA ESA - Processing & Licence: Judy SchmidtExplanation: Stars are forming in the gigantic dust pillar called the Cone Nebula. Cones pillars and majestic flowing shapes abound in stellar nurseries where natal clouds of gas and dust are buffeted by energetic winds from newborn stars. The Cone Nebula a well-known example lies within the bright galactic star-forming region NGC 2264. The Cone was captured in unprecedented detail in this close-up composite of several observations from the Earth-orbiting Hubble Space Telescope. While the Cone Nebula about 2500 light-years away in Monoceros is around 7 light-years long the region pictured here surrounding the cones blunted head is a mere 2.5 light-years across. In our neck of the galaxy that distance is just over half way from our Sun to its nearest stellar neighbors in the Alpha Centauri star system. The massive star NGC 2264 IRS seen by Hubbles infrared camera in 1997 is the likely source of the wind sculpting the Cone Nebula and lies off the top of the image. The Cone Nebulas reddish veil is produced by dust and glowing hydrogen gas.

tweet_raw: 🌐 Reflecting on 2023 #Filecoins journey was marked by significant strides in technology and adoption. A surge in active storage deals and the launch of the Filecoin Virtual Machine (#FVM) set a foundation for growth.Lets delve into the latest 2023 insights from the State of Filecoin by @FilecoinTLDR and explore what lies ahead in 2024! Ready? ⤵️2023 Retrospective:▫️ Storage Boom: Active deals soared to 1800 PiB with 20% storage utilization.▫️ FVM Launch: Introduced FIL lending contributing 11% to total collateral locked by Storage Providers with Total Value Locked hitting $200M.▫️ Retrievals: Enhanced reliability and standout releases from @FilecoinSaturn (3000+ nodes sub-60ms TTFB) and @FilecoinStation.▫️ Compute Triumphs: Real-world utility demonstrated by @BacalhauProject and others.Themes for 2024:▫️ Synergies: Expect Filecoin to seamlessly integrate with compute #AI and #DePIN networks for collaborative growth.▫️ Web2 Enterprise Data Storage: Strengthened offerings from teams like @BanyanComputer @SealStorage and Steeldome cater to the unique needs of enterprise clients.▫️ DeFi on the Rise: Continued growth in on-chain DeFi protocols including DEXes Oracles and CDPs.Looking Ahead to 2024:▫️ Synergies Galore: Filecoins improvements enable seamless interaction with other ecosystems promising many use cases.▫️ Web2 Enterprise Solutions: Teams like @BanyanComputer @SealStorage and Steeldome address enterprise needs offering adaptability and compatibility.▫️ On-chain DeFi Surge: More services including @SushiSwap and @Uniswap bring diverse DeFi offerings on-chain expanding the ecosystem.In 2024 Filecoin anticipates widespread adoption particularly in compute AI and targeted enterprise sectors. On-chain service revenue and growing DeFi activities are set to propel Filecoin into its next remarkable growth phase. ✈️Eager for more details? Read the full report: filecointldr.io/article/stat…
